<p>My goal is to show some content after a user has shared a link on Facebook.</p>  <p>I'm trying to achieve this using Facebook Javascript SDK. This code is actually working:</p>  <pre><code>$.ajaxSetup({ cache: true }); $.getScript('//connect.facebook.net/en_US/sdk.js', function(){     FB.init({         appId: '...',         version: 'v2.4'     }); });  $('body').on('click', '.facebook-share', function(e){      e.preventDefault();      FB.ui({         method: 'feed',         link: 'http://website.com/',         caption: 'An example caption',     }, function(response){          console.log(response);      });  }); </code></pre>  <p>This seems to work only if the link (<a href="http://website.com/" rel="nofollow">http://website.com/</a>), the site URL inside the Facebook app, and the domain where the function is triggered, match.</p>  <p>Is it possible to make it work also if I want to share a different link which does not match the current website from where the function is actually triggered?</p>